{
  "texts": [
    "Interestingly, for super-critical regions where κ > 1 (these correspond to highly demagnified saddle-point or maximum images), the anisotropic magnification (stretching) due to the shear changes direction by π/2 due to the 1κ term being negative (see Eq.",
    "(76) of Saha et al. 2024).",
    "This is clearly seen as the horizontal caustic structures for κ < 1 become vertical for κ > 1.",
    "These diverse caustic structures have an impact on the microlensing effect present in observations, i.e.",
    "through light curves and magnification probability distributions of flux ratios (see the next section)."
  ]
}